cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Network Performance Measurement and Analysis Experiment
abstract: This dataset contains the outputs from an experiment designed to characterize
  network performance characteristics across multiple nodes (rapla, tapa, valga).
  The methodology involved establishing secure remote access via SSH key configuration,
  followed by dependency installation using Rust tools. Subsequent runs utilized Time-Based
  Flow Control and Network Emulation to manipulate latency parameters while measuring
  data transfer rates. Data generation included randomized byte sequences for analysis,
  alongside client and server processes configured with varying scheduling and QoS
  settings. The experiment ultimately produced network traffic capture data and visualization
  outputs, facilitating performance evaluation across the defined infrastructure.
